This paper uses Twitter data to explore the topics of discussion of politicians, specifically the U.S. President and State Governors, and applies agenda-setting theory to describe the patterns of daily political discussion. The paper also examines the communication styles of Republican and Democrat Governors and reconstructs networks of occurrences of Governors' hashtags and keywords related to political issues. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
